      TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR USE, REPRODUCTION, AND DISTRIBUTION

1. Terminology

   "Software" refers exclusively to the contents of the Stackpress 
   repository, including all packages, plugins, generators, templates, 
   configurations, specifications, and related components contained 
   therein. Software, libraries, frameworks, packages, services, or 
   projects maintained under separate repositories or distributed under 
   separate licenses are not considered part of the Software and remain 
   governed by their respective licenses.

   "Licensee" means any individual, organization, company, government 
   entity, or other party utilizing the Software.

   "Product" means any application, platform, website, service, software 
   offering, SaaS offering, commercial solution, or other customer-facing 
   system developed using the Software.

   "Internal Use" means use of the Software exclusively within an 
   organization for internal operations, administration, infrastructure, 
   tooling, reporting, monitoring, development, or similar 
   non-customer-facing purposes.

   "Annual Gross Revenue" means the total revenue generated by a Product 
   during a twelve-month period before deductions, expenses, taxes, 
   commissions, refunds, discounts, or other adjustments.

   "Commercial Threshold" means Annual Gross Revenue exceeding 
   $1,000,000 USD generated by a Product.

   "Commercial Licensing Agreement" means a separate written agreement 
   executed between the Licensor and the Licensee authorizing continued 
   use of the Software after a Product exceeds the Commercial Threshold.

   "Licensor" means the copyright holder and owner of the Software.

2. The Software is developed and maintained by the Licensor and is made 
   available to the community in good faith. The purpose of this license 
   is not to impose automatic royalties, mandatory revenue sharing, or 
   fixed commercial fees. The purpose of this license is to preserve the 
   opportunity for a commercial relationship when the Software becomes 
   materially important to a successful Product.

3. Free Use. The Licensee may use, modify, distribute, and commercially 
   exploit the Software without charge provided that no Product exceeds 
   the Commercial Threshold. No registration, attribution, notification, 
   or payment is required below the Commercial Threshold.

4. When a Product exceeds the Commercial Threshold, the Licensee must
   notify the Licensor within 90 days, enter into good-faith discussions 
   regarding a Commercial Licensing Agreement, and execute a Commercial 
   Licensing Agreement within 180 days. Continued use of the Software 
   beyond the Commercial Threshold without a Commercial Licensing 
   Agreement constitutes a violation of this license.

5. Exemption. Products and systems utilized exclusively for Internal Use 
   are exempt from the Commercial Threshold requirements. This license 
   is intended to apply only to customer-facing Products and services.

6. The purpose of a Commercial Licensing Agreement is to establish an 
   ongoing commercial relationship once a Product exceeds the Commercial 
   Threshold. Commercial Licensing Agreements are negotiated individually 
   and in good faith. Commercial terms may vary in your favor based on 
   product revenue, product maturity, dependency upon the Software, 
   funding status, strategic value, existing relationship between the 
   parties, and other relevant business considerations. The Licensor is 
   not obligated to offer identical terms to all Licensees. Commercial 
   consideration may include fixed annual licensing fees, support 
   agreements, consulting arrangements, attribution, strategic 
   partnerships, other mutually agreed exchanges of value, or any 
   combination thereof. The specific terms of each Commercial Licensing 
   Agreement are determined on a case-by-case basis.

7. A Licensee may cease utilizing the Software at any time. If the 
   Software is removed from a Product and is no longer utilized, no 
   future Commercial Licensing Agreement is required. Nothing in this 
   license prevents a Licensee from replacing, rewriting, or migrating 
   away from the Software.

8. A Licensee may not avoid obligations under this license through 
   transfer, assignment, resale, sublicensing, white-label arrangements, 
   or similar structures. The party directly utilizing the Software 
   remains responsible for compliance with this license.

GUIDING PRINCIPLE

The Software is free to use until it becomes commercially significant.
When a Product exceeds the Commercial Threshold, the Licensee does not 
automatically owe a royalty, revenue share, or predetermined fee. 
Instead, continued use requires a Commercial Licensing Agreement so that 
both parties have the opportunity to establish a commercial relationship 
appropriate to the value created, the circumstances of the business, and 
the role the Software plays within the Product.